## INDIA 
&nbsp;  
The timeseries charts for northeastern India show a steady increase for both NO2 and SO2 from 2005-2018, which then leveled off, perhaps due to the deployment of air pollution control technology. The significant drop in both SO2 and NO2 in 2020 is most likely the result of the prolonged COVID-19 lockdown in India that resulted in a reduction in fossil fuel combustion.
